\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \fi-461\li461\ri0\sa240\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin461\itap0\pararsid16258992 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Can I ask you when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 1888. 23}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \super\insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 rd}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005  of August.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Whereabouts were you born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Leyton in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Essex{\*\xmlclose}.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 And you spent all your early days there, did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 No, I was only there for two years. 1890 my father came to Hanwell.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 I see. What was your father's job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Well he was a kind of contractor in those days, he did removi
ng, and strictly speaking I don't know how he really came to Ealing because it is quite a distance away. He had his horse and van to dispose of and somehow or other a surveyor, named Charley Jones, quite a nice man. He got in touch with him and said "Well
 
I will give you ten pounds for your horse and I will give you a job". That's a very funny way of doing but that's just how it happened. But apart from that I can't tell you any more, from that point of view. But any case he settled into Hanwell and that w
as it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 What sort of house did you have in Hanwell?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Oh just an ordinary type of terrace house, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 How many rooms were there?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 I don't know, there must have been three - two or three upstairs I suppose and about three down below.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 How many brothers and sisters had you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 
Well we used to crowd a bit then you know, there was seven of us besides Mother and Father. A big family. Pretty regular in those days! But not so today. Not so today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Whereabouts were you in your family, were they mostly older or mostly younger than you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 
Well. We haven't been out of Hanwell you know since 1890. Various little places we used to move, in those days you could move from here to there and you know, well you just used to decide - oh we
ll I will go somewhere else - and that was it. I can't tell you the real circumstances, you know, we used to move, the whole family, including the rabbits and the chickens!
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Oh you had livestock as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Had you a garden usually?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 
No, we had quite a big allotment 40 rods as a matter of fact. 40 rabbits we had, six goats. And that was not too far away, of course it is all built on now and us youngsters, boys, were detailed to look after these goats you know. Well at end of th
e field was a gravel pit, which was about 15' deep. Well unfortunately one day, when I was on duty, one fell over the face of the cliff! My Dad - he gave me a real hiding! I got so frightened because he left me nearly unconscious - he didn't touch me any 
more after that!
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 I suppose you milked your goats did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 
Oh, for kiddies, we were more or less brought up on goats milk you know. My father used to dress the skins and somebody used to come along and collect them. And we had rugs, rugs of them. Oh yes. Those six goats, everybody knew them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Had you vegetables at all on your allotment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 
Yes, well they provided us with everything we wanted - 40 rods near enough. Of course the land was there then, which it isn't today. But I tell you it's 
all built on now. Well I have got it all down here as a matter of fact. Originally it was in manuscript, I tell you doctor, he typed these out for me. Kept a copy himself in the reference library. Can stop there, indefinitely, you can't talk about 100 yea
r
s. Any case, he was more than pleased with them. Very matter of fact language, well I said to him I said don't claim this to be of any literary merit, but as a matter of fact he said "That's just what I want". "We get tired of what they call literary jarg
on, the same old whatsername. That's somewhat different to what we have been used to" so that suited him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Were your parents interested in this sort of thing at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Oh no, this was entirely my own initiative. Yes, I've lived in Hanwell quite a lo
ng while, and I thought in 1944, I thought to myself, well I don't know, I have lived in Hanwell so long I think I will put my experiences down, I had seen quite a lot you know - mostly fun you know. I have had a lot of fun in Hanwell. I thought to meself
 I will put it down on pencil and paper. Well I did, and I tell eventually I added to it, and it\rquote s unique in its way, it\rquote 
s unique in its way. So far as I know there is nothing like it round about Hanwell. At least I have not met anybody that has been that way inclined. You know it was quite my own initiative.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 How old were you when you started school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Oh the usual age of about five I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Which school was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 The old St. Marks School down the road there, still in existence, 1855, well over 100 years, one of the old type of primary schools.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Infants boys and girls were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 It stood there, well of course they had the boys section and the girls section, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 How many teachers were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Well we had - well if I 
was to say we had six teachers, you know, girls and boys and of course we had seven standards, that's how we used to classify them, 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7. The sixth and seventh were combined, the headmaster always took those. Strictly speaking we must have 
had five or six school teachers. Some were tough and some were not.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Were they strict on the whole would you say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Well, what I can I talk about, were they strict? Well they used to use the cane, but we used to say to ourselves well I suppose we de
served it, and that was it. But strictly speaking I think that they were really good.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 You do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Oh yes. I got on very well with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 How did you enjoy school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Well everything except History. History I wasn't too keen on. I was an expe
rt on map drawing, the headmaster used to get me out the cartridge paper in front of the class and say "That's right, get on with this one" Well if you know anything about the map of Italy or anything like that it's not at all easy when you have got to in
clude the mountains and the currents and so many - in any case I would stand out there on my own and he let me get on with it! Although strictly speaking, well he left it to me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Had you games organised at school at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Well in those days we hadn't got the variety of games as what you've got today. Netball was unknown for a start, but er -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 What did you play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Oh I played football. Yes, I played football. Yes. There's an old lady still living in Hanwell, I'm hoping to get that photograph 
that she's got, 1896. Well, that Boys' football team went clean through the season without a defeat and finished up with winning what they call the Dewar's Shield. Dewars, the whisky people, still in existence, well they presented us with a local shield. 
We won that outright. I think our best season was 1896 - now that's a long while ago.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 You would spend your evenings playing football would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Well, I used to, that is quite true.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 What other sort of things would you do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Well. If you 
are going to talk about hobbies, well there wasn't much then cricket and football and chasing all over the surroundings, you know. Well we spent most of our time out of doors, we did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 How about in the winter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Well in the winter well - from what 
I remember I used to be very fond of me books. A greater reader in me time, I have always been more or less satisfied I think, more satisfied perhaps than what the youngsters are today. I never chased, what I call chased about. No I was quite content to s
it at home with me brothers and sisters, playing with them, or having a game together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Had you many books and newspapers in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Well I gradually built them up myself. I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 That was good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Yes. I gradually built them up myself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Had your father a newspaper?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 
Well, we had, there is a paper still running now, called "The People" well we had that one of a Sunday, and "Lloyds News" that was another one. The daily papers well we didn't worry about. If we had a Sunday paper, e
verybody seemed to be satisfied. Including my father, you know, daily papers we didn't worry too much about. Of course, even the "Daily Mail" has only been running about 60 or 50 years. They are comparatively modern. Those papers weren't in existence. I c
an't tell you the name of the daily papers then but there certainly wasn't many. But if we had that Sunday paper, well I tell you, "Lloyds News" or "The People" we were quite satisfied for the week. Quite satisfied.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Had your parents any outside interests?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 
Well no. They didn't have much chance. In those days they were busy with the old wash tub. And when they got seven or eight youngsters to look after - you don't want telling that they had a full day! No, they had a full day.
\par 
\par Year 1890 I arrived at Hanwell at the age of two and went to live in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Maunder Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. My first recollection was that my father sold his horse for }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10243417 \'a3}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 10 and obtained employment with Mr. Charles Jones on the Ealing Town Council as a gardener. His chief job was to plant trees in the
 various roads as they were made up and built over.
\par My father next obtained 40 rods of allotment on top of what was Mr. Charles Macklin's gravel pit which is at present {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Montague Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
. I well remember 1891 the Great Frost when I used to help my sister Nell and brothers to carry water from the stand pipe at the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Boston Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} end of 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Maunder Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. My mother used to pay 2d. per bucket from the Council water cart when we could not supply her with enough.
\par Sister May had arrived and we had no water in the house to give her first wash and the person next door could have all she wanted so she took in washing without paying for it.
\par We next moved to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Springfield Avenue{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, opposite where St. Anne's School stands now. They were some of the best times in my life, school days. T
hings were uneventful until I reached Standard 3 when I received a taste of Mr. ?\rquote s left hand swish of the cane. His son Bert once shied an ink pot at him, and goodness knows what happened when his father got him home!
\par I always thought that Standard 3 and 
4 were the most solid learning classes of all in the old national school. Mr. George Harwood was my old schoolmaster in Standard 6 and 7, in Standard 4 I was employed as an expert map drawer. I used to be allowed to exhibit to the class, pinned on the bla
ckboard, maps 3 foot square. I was also an expert in geography as much as anything else.
\par 
\par I got a bit unruly towards twelve years of age and I well remember having twelve strokes from Mr. Harwood. At the age of eleven and a half I obtained a job for a Mr. Clarke, greengrocer, Hanwell Broadway, on Saturday mornings, wages 6d.
\par At twelve and a half I went to work full time for him at 3/6d. a week and a basket of vegetables.
\par We used to work on the round in the mornings, afternoons in the gardens and orchards, now the Hanwell Train Depot. We also had geese to take and chickens as our last job every afternoon.
\par I was there three and a half years, all day. My mouth organ was a good companion on a Saturday night when we had a lonely journey to the Old Hermitage next t
o the Rectory. On Sundays we played what we called Sunday league football and I well remember when Patrol Policeman Mead took our ball from us and we drew names as to who was to go to the police station and collect it. I was unlucky and very timorously we
n
t to collect this ball. Sergeant? the Station Master that day, as soon as he saw me said in his manner "What do you want?" I said "I've come for my ball", "Oh, have you, have you" to P.C. Mead "Give him his ball, do the necessary!" whereupon P.C.Mead cuff
ed me behind the ear with his glove and booted me in the pants and away I went down the steps, ball and all. I never realized that a bobby's glove could hurt so much but I wasn't surprised at his foot. However, Sunday league football still carried on.

\par And I
 played a good game at left back and finished up at outside left. My brother Alf played fast at centre forward. Mr. Cook, a milkman, had a lovely lot of cows at that time turned out in the field. His son Charlie worked for Owen Bishop, the butcher on the 
B}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15166971\charrsid12671005 r}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 
oardway. One Easter Monday he cut off the curls of a chubby fifteen year old with curls to the shoulder. That got him the sack
\par 
\par I well remember the stage coach from {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Oxford{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}London{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose}. Mr. Frank Spiers was the cab and he always played his posthorn when he arrived at the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Brent{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Bridge
{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} which divides Southall and Hanwell. This would signal for his wife to bring him along his dinner or tea. We always ran to meet the coach when we could.
\par At about the same time the horse buses came along. Their stables were in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Boston Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
, opposite the Victoria Public House. After that came the London United Tramways which were opening in 1902. The cream and blue paint looked very nice but they used to rattle very much.
\par I well remember about 200 Irish navies being employed on breaking up the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Main Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. Three men with sledge hammers and I }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15166971\charrsid12671005 had }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 
to hold the peg. I think this is the reason why we have so many Catholics in Hanwell and Irish tram drivers. The next thing I remember was the foundation of the Hanwell and District Horticultural
 Society. We used to hold monthly meetings and discussions. I still have in my possession a certificate awarded to me for some tomatoes in pots. I also used to show chrysanthemums 13" across.
\par I also grew cyclamens and geraniums.
\par Mr. Seward of Hill Farm, {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Boston Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
, the one time rate collector and I worked for him for fourteen years followed by three years war service. And when I came back Mr. Seward said he would not carry on any longer. Under Mr. Shrimpton, Mr. Sewards's foreman, until he left in 1910, I 
had a pleasant time in the greenhouses although I worked 70 hours a week.
\par I used to like my trips with him to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Crystal{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Palace{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} to show chrysant}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15166971\charrsid12671005 h}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 emums and to the Horti}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15166971\charrsid12671005 cultural}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005  Hall in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Vincent Square{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} to show cyclamens. Mr. Seward also kept thirty cows and seve
n acres of orchard. He had a very fine Shorthorn bull, a real terror out in the field. He also had a horse which retired at thirty-two years.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 I wondered how you found your first job with Mr. Clark?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Well, well in the ordinary course, you know wh
at it is, well what used to happen was this. Mum was glad of whatever she could get and I can't really tell how I started that job, it was in a greengrocers shop. Well in the ordinary course we used to drop into a job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 And you started after leaving school then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 
Oh, I was, yes. Twelve years of age, twelve and half, something like that. The schoolmaster didn't like it, no. He said "All my best boys go" you know. He was very struck with my handwriting. He said to my mother he said "Your boy writes a
 lovely Civil Service hand, he is too good for what they call a knock about job" you know, but that's what happened in those days and that was it. My Mum was glad of the few shillings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Would you have stayed on if you had had any opportunity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Well the opportunities, well I won't say that they weren't there. But not to the extent as what they are today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Well when we got to the Seventh Standard, well we used to, you know, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15166971\charrsid12671005 go }
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 back into work of some description.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 How did you enjoy work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Oh I was happy as a kid! Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 The hours were fairly long though, weren't they, with Mr. Clark?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 8}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}
{\xmlattrvalue 0}}}Eight o'clock{\*\xmlclose} till six, something like that. Well they were shop hours then you know. Which is a bit longer than what they are today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 It is, isn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 
You know, of course on Saturday, there was a clear eight to eight. That was in those days, yes. No forty hour then you know, I don't know any trade at all that worked forty hours. Unless it was the, unless it was {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Whitehall{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}!
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 How did you find your next job? You said you moved then. Didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 
I moved into some greenhouses on the exact spot as where you are sitting now! We used to buy our tomatoes from the people that owned these greenhouses and the job was going at some 
time or another and I got into it. Eventually I did seventeen years in the greenhouses, I took over in the finish.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 What were they growing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Tomatoes, chrysanths, cyclamen, and geraniums, that's what we used to grow.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Who owned them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 A man named Seward S - E - W - A - R - D. But he was a well known}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15166971\charrsid12671005  }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 local man then, he was. They also had thirty cows. That street of houses that you see down there, that used to be our paddock. Where the horses and the cows used to be. And you can see the cros
s road at the top there, well that is as far as the paddock used to go. Seventeen years I was there. Of course the Big War came along, that took up nearly four years of my time, when I came back, well, the Boss was fairly well off, "I am sorry John" he sa
id "But I don't feel like carrying on any more." He said "I will give you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10243417 \'a3}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 
2 a week until you get a fresh job". Well I managed to get on the railway. A chum of mine came along and told me there was a job there. I was 38 at Paddington, as what they call a Railway }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15166971\charrsid12671005 c}
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 ellarman, in amongst the wines and spirits.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 He was a good employer, Mr. Seward, was he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Yes, all right, yes he was quite good, as they went in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 How many people had he working for him altogether?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Oh, including the gr
ound pit me, we used to have gravel pits out there, I suppose he had a dozen men all told. Then we had the cowman, who used to look after the cows, and we had the milkroundsman as well. Oh there could have been a dozen of us altogether.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Quite a decent sized little business.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Oh it was a business! Well this place, I tell you, this is the exact spot where it stood, where we are now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Strange isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Yes, I have come back to where I almost started. After sixty five years I have come back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Were your parents Church or Chapel goers at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Well strictly speaking I don't remember them being connected with anything much. Beyond that in the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname 
address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Westminster Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, down there, we used to have a {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Baptist{\*\xmlclose} 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}Church{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, it's pulled down now, it was we
ll over a hundred years old and suffering from dry rot when it was pulled down. Well, we used to go there to Sunday School and my mother used to belong to the Mothers Union. Well that's the only real association that my parents had really with the Church,
 but you see they didn't force us to do anything at all, you know, just let us carry on. Well eventually, well I got that way, that I attached meself to the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Old{\*\xmlclose}
 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Parish{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}Church{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 How old would you have been then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Yes, the Parish of St. Mary's. Well
 I was well in everything at the age of 17. Oh yes. Now that's the church out in the fields over there. It is still in existence 1862 that church was. And I spent well over fifty years over there I did. Until I got this side of the parish and my feet turn
ed out to be no good, I found I had to pack it up, and now I can't go there at all much because of the awkward hours. Each time I go over there I am late for either dinner or supper and it puts things out of gear. Well now I go to 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}St. Thomas{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}'s just up the road. Yes, that's sixty years I have been attached to that }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15166971\charrsid12671005 c}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 hurch really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Had it anything on the week evenings, any boys clubs or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Well this is what happened. St. Mary's had a really good boys club. We had, of course we had got the groun
d then, the ground to play on in those days. And then believe it or not we had eight football teams.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Gosh! That's huge!
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 You couldn't do it today! Eight football teams and three cricket teams. Oh we were satisfied with that. We had got no other 
subsidiaries. Of course one of the conditions was that we attended the Bible Class, well none of us grumbled about that. Well it was part and parcel of the set up. Yes, we had -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Quite a thriving concern.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 It was well known in Hanwell, St. Mary's 
Church Club, oh yes, eight football teams. And well I still carried on playing football after that, you know. And when I made up my mind to get married, I thought meself well I won't take any chances so I packed up playing football, I did three years with
 the referee's whistle, automatically - you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 How did you meet your wife?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Well er - Her mother became a widow, living at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Bangor
{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}North Wales{\*\xmlclose}. Mind you there was ten youngsters her mother couldn't cope you see. The result was most of them go
t scattered about and in those days for a girl, there wasn't much else apart from domestic service. Well she came to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}London{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 along with her sister and then they went in domestic service. And her sister had got friendly with my brother, I got friendly with her sister, and the result was brothers and sisters got married! So that's all I can tell you about that! 1913 that was.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 They lived round here did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Oh yes. Lived here ever since in Hanwell. I still lived in Hanwell all that time. I was married in that }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15166971\charrsid12671005 c}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 hurch. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Had you saved up a long time?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Well I did save really. Up to a point. Because I was working seven days a week. You know, seven days a week. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6447358\charrsid12671005 \{blank\} s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 o strictly speaking we couldn't go anywhere much. But I managed to save }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10243417 \'a3}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 90 well that was a lot - you'd be surprised. Well I set up three rooms, quite good, quite good. Yes. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10243417 \'a3}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 90 well in those days -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 All right wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 You can't do much with it now can you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Not so much as you could do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Yes, I well remember that figure. Eventually the boy and the girl came along, well that was quite good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 After the war I suppose, that was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 The girl came during the War. Oh I forget now, 1915 or 16, something like that. And the boy he was quite late, 1925. Well t
he girl is well over, is 52 now or thereabouts and the boy is 43. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15166971\charrsid12671005 W}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 
ell they're placed pretty well, you know what I mean to say, as placements go, he has got quite a good job at Marconi's.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 I suppose your wife stopped working after she got married.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Oh yes she certainly did! Oh yes she certainly stopped working then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Who budgeted in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 
When the War of course continued, she went out to McCleans, down there, she thought to herself "Well I will do my bit" and that was it. McCleans the, you know the people down there.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Had you much of a social life, music hall or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 
Well, we had, the nearest one was Ealing Theatre, well that today, well it's gone through quite a number of changes. It went from Ealing Theatre
, we used to have some really good straight plays there, you know, the real old fashioned type that, you know, we could sit down and enjoy. 6d. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15166971\charrsid12671005 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005  packet of peanuts and orange peel (?) and this that and the other. Everything went up. But we used to enjoy it. And our regular Pantomime once a year. Dan Leno and Herbert Campbell, two famous old com}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15166971\charrsid12671005 edians}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 , they used to come, oh yes. Go in at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 19}}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 45}}}quarter to eight{\*\xmlclose} and come out at ten minutes to twelve! Now there's an evening for you!
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Very long.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 If you get t
wo hours entertainment now of a night you have had a long while, haven't you. In any case, well, eventually Ealing Theatre, Ealing Hippodrome, well it was turned into a cinema after that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Had you any holidays as children, away from home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Well ho
lidays, well in those days we didn't have them. No we didn't. Firstly the wages, and the big families you know, it wasn't really possible. But er there used to be a society in Ealing called Ealing St. Johns Temperance. Well they would run excursions perha
ps twice a year, and if we had a day down at the seaside - oh - we had had - our holiday!
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 You had had a holiday!
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 That suited us, we were satisfied. Strange to relate is we were satisfied. Going down to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Worthing
{\*\xmlclose} or {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Margate{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} or somewhere. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Had you Sunday School outings at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 
Yes, we had our regular Sunday School outings, but believe it or not, well we never went any distance really, mostly out to Richmond Park, to the other side of Richmond Park, or somewhere down there, that was
 our school outing. Well the different tradesmen used to have horses and vans, and they would take us in these horses and vans. That's how we used to - our Sunday Schools. We never went by train on our Sunday School outings, no, we didn't do that. These h
orses and vans, the different tradesmen would come along and collect us up, perhaps 50 of us, and we would have the usual races and this that and the other. You know, what you have at a kiddies Sunday School outing. We were satisfied.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Had you any spending money as children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 (Big laughs) Well if we had sixpence I suppose we were lucky. Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 I suppose you would spend it on sweets would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Well, sweets and what we used to call the Hokey Pokey man, he would come round with a barrel on a Sunday. No, -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 How about after you started work, I suppose you handed your wage over to your mother did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Well I did, but I think I had about sixpence of it back!
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Well we were quite happy you know really, we were doing out bit. O
f course Mother always used to buy our clothes. Whatever we wanted. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 How about after you were married, I suppose your wife was in charge of the household budget was she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Well that is quite true. Quite true. Yes, she was always good. Well 
to tell you candidly people say "Oh why do you do it?" or "Why did you do it?" I used to hand my w}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15166971\charrsid12671005 age packet over just like that. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 (Slapped hand on table!)
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Well if she could do it, that was okay.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 I never went short. She knew just how the money we
nt and it suited me you know, it didn't worry me a bit. If I wanted a shilling or two for pocket money, well it was there. Yes. It didn't worry me a bit, once I had handed that over, well we used to take the week right through, well we got through life al
l right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Well that's the main thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 I did it for forty-three years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 A long time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 
Well that was all right, I let my wife have it, you know, whatever there was there, that was it. Oh yes, it never worried me a bit, as long as the money was in the home, I was satisfied. And the kiddies didn't go short.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Were your parents strict with you as children?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Well not really, I can't say that they were strict. Although my father had got the old fashioned strap! When we wanted the strap w
e had it! I supposed we deserved it and that was it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 What sort of things were you punished for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Well I tell you, the biggest hiding I had was when I let the goat fall over the cliff. Yes, I never had a bigger hiding than that}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15166971\charrsid12671005 . }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 No. They was all r
ight. They was all right. He died in 1914. But they was all right. And I don't remember a more even tempered man in all my life. Very}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12532078\charrsid12671005 ,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6447358\charrsid12671005  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 very seldom saw him in what I call a rage. If I can finish up like him well I will be satisfied. I will be satisfied. I never known a more even tempered man.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Would you say that your parents were comfortably off? They weren't well off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 No, not really. No. My father was only in the 30/- stage. No, we weren't well off by any means. Oh no no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 You never went short though did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 
No, not really. I tell you we always had the vegetables to fall back on. We never had to buy them. Well my mother, to be quite candid about it, went for the cheapest cuts, and she knew how to dish it up. Well in those days you could 
get, what they called a four-hock of bacon, eight pounds, that was the weight of it. Well it was only 4d. a pound. What would you pay today?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 An awful lot more.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 That 8 lbs, that covered all our family and there were quite a lot over, oh that was
 a real bargain job that was. If we had a hock of bacon there was nothing more tasty than that. Nothing more tasty than that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 How many times a week would you have meat? Every day or just -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 I believe so. Yes, we never went without a mid-day meal
, not really. Us kids used to come home and it was always there. It might have been in the nature of a stew or something like that, but never mind it was always, as far as I know there was always a big meal about.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Would your father have his mid-day meal with you or would he have a meal in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Well he used to take his daily sandwiches with him, you see, for mid-day, and come home to a meal at night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Would you actually see much of him then, if he was working long hours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Well I don't know what his job was, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12532078\charrsid12671005 cos }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 
this was in Ealing, not in Hanwell, he worked in Ealing. As the road was what we call "adopted" made up by the council, him and a chum, Jack Smart, used to plant the trees all through the borough. Every road that was made up
 in Ealing my father planted the trees, and anybody grumbling about the leaves in October - well they better blame my old Dad for that. But now we have got a new Superintendent, or Director of Parks, he decided that all these big trees have got to come do
wn, and now they are planting flowering cherries. Quite young ones, they'll grow up you see. The old big trees that you can see in the roads now, you can see them outside there, well they are a thing of the past.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 You told me that you were 1 of 7 children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Quite true, 7 in the family
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 I wonder if you could tell me the order of the children and the spaces between them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Well, not a great lot, takes a bit of working out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Have you any idea how old your father was when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 I can work that out. He died at the age of 72.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 So he was 42 when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 You told me that before you moved to Hanwell he'd been a contractor. Do you know if he had any other job before he became a contractor?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Oh, yes, he was a head gardener to Claybury Hall in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Essex{\*\xmlclose}
. Now that's an enormous great mental home, now. run by the L.C.C. As far as I know he had 16 gardeners under him there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 And that was before he became a contractor?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 That's right, before he branched out on his own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Did he ever do any casual or part-time jobs? Besides his main\'85
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Well, of course, a contractor was more or less \'85 you know what I mean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 I know what you mean but it was full-time work, of course?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Oh, certainly, it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 I wondered if he had any extra part-time jobs that you know of?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 No, no, as far as I know that was his full-time job, until he came to live}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12532078\charrsid12671005  here. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 When he became a gardener again, I believe?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Yes, he became \'85 well, planting trees. A landscape man. That's the right word for it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Did he continue in that work until he passed over?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Yes for 28 years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Do you remember his ever being out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Never. No, no, that was, 28 years or thereabouts.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 How old was your mother when you were born? So your mother was about 32. Had she worked before she married your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Oh, certainly she did. For 35 years she worked for in the City.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 What sort of work was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 I think it was tie-making, or something like that. Y
ou know, making ties when they made them by hand. And all the while she was there she never missed a Lord Mayor's Show. Well, it's off the river, see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Did she continue working after she was married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Oh, no. No, no, she finished work then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Did she ever go back to work at any later stage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 No, not with a family like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 In your house where you lived in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Maunder Road
{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} - about how many rooms were there in that house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Well, there could have been 3 bedrooms, and there's the and wha
t we used to call the parlour, you know, kitchen and a scullery. Just an ordinary terraced house of those days. Coming up to 90 years old, those houses.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Did you have one room that you kept as a special room, you know, a front room that wasn't used every day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Well, of course, in those days there was always what we call the front room. That was a Sunday room, I can't call it anything else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Only used to Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Well, mostly on Sundays, you know. Every house had their front parlour and that was what it was used for.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Did you have anyone like relatives, or lodgers, living with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 No, no, not with a family like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 So your mother didn't have anyone helping her? She did all the work herself, did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Quite so. 'Course, as most of us chaps grew up, you know, we did our bit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Do you remember if your mother had a particular routine for cleaning the house; certain rooms on certain days, or anything like that?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 I can't tell you any particular routine, beyond washin
g day. You know what Monday is, don't you? Monday had to be washing day. And at 2.30, I don't remember her ever missing, her Mothers' Meeting in the afternoon. People talk about the amount of work they do today, but she'd do the washing for all of us on t
he Monday and in the afternoon she always had that free.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 And she always went to that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 She went to her Mother's }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12532078\charrsid12671005 M}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 eeting. They call it Mothers' {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Union{\*\xmlclose}, now, don't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Yes. Did she make any clothes for the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Well, so far as I know she did her best. Probably she made the under-clothes for us, for the kiddies, 'cos she had to buy the \'85
 you know, top clothes for all of us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Do you know where she bought the clothes? Were they from shops, or traders, or clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Well, I'll be quite candid about it. In those days everything had to be cheap. She used to go to a shop in 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}West Ealing{\*\xmlclose} \'85 I'll be quite clear about it \'85 pawnbrokers and always, almost without fail \'85 She couldn't help it, she hadn't got the money to spend. Secondhand clothe
s. That's all I can say about it. And that's how people lived in those days. I'm talking about the working class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Did she ever have any new clothes that she bought, or was it all second-hand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 I can't tell you that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 What about shoes? Were they secondhand, as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Well to my knowledge. The recognised shoe shops that you see now in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}West Ealing{\*\xmlclose}
 were not there, so we had to get them at that particular shop with very few exceptions to my knowledge. So they were more likely secondhand, perhaps, than what they were new.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 In the household work, do you remember your father doing anything to help actually in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Well, no. I wouldn't say he did. He wasn't very good in the sense of the word. He'd got his outside interests which mea
nt forty yards of allotment, it's quite a hefty job. We had 40 rabbits and 6 goats and his work outside all appertaining to us, you know, it all came into the house. He was pretty busy outside, we didn't expect him to ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 To do things in the house. no. If there was a bit of decorating to be done, or repair work did he do that, or did your mother do that?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Well, as far as I know the landlord used to do that, I don't remember that we had to do it in those days. We weren't expected to do it.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Do
 you remember if he did anything actually for the children, I mean for you and your brothers and sisters in the way of putting you to bed, or dressing you or undressing you, reading you stories?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 No, I don't remember that part about it, but he didn't \'85 he never \'85 used to go out, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Well, he was very busy with his outside work, wasn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 It was a 12 hour day, you know, {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 18}}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}}6 o'clock{\*\xmlclose} 'till 6 at the Council. By the time he got home at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 18}}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 30}}}half past 6{\*\xmlclose}, {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 19}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 30}}}half past 7
{\*\xmlclose}, he was a tired man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Did y
ou have any particular job that you had to do? I know you had to look after the goats. Was there anything else you had to do in the way of helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Well, I well remember a regular job I used to do cleaning the forks and the spoons on a Saturday morni
ng. Apart from that, well, I went out to work at the age of 12}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12671005  1/2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 
 you know. But a regular job, as far as I know that was my job on a Saturday, cleaning the forks and spoons. I don't remember anything other, particularly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 What about the other brothers and sisters, did they have particular jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 
Well, you know, it was generally, 'do this' and 'do that' between the lot of us, I think. No I don't think they had anything particular. Most of them started work early, you know. My elder sister, well, sh
e's 88 she went to work quite early, at that age we used to leave school at 12 and 13 and this, that and the other. And no question of you were going to stop at school 'till you were 18, nothing like that. We had to go out and earn those few shillings.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 When you were a schoolboy, were you expected to go to bed at a certain time? Were your parents particular about you being in and in bed?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 No, I don't remember any restrictions like that, but we were never far from home, you know, not after tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Did you put yourself to bed and did you see to it that you got yourself to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 
Well, we all did as far as we were able, according to our ages. As soon as you might say, you know, off your mother's lap, you did for yourself. It didn't do us any harm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 When you were a child, who did you share your bedroom with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 
Oh, I say (laughter) You're talking about a bed! I don't know, there were two at the top and two at the bottom. That was how they used to do it, you know. We had to work out our 3 bedrooms. There was my Mum and Dad and the rest of us (laughter)\'85
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 And the rest of you in the two beds?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Well, that was how people lived in those days, two or 3 at the top and 2 or 3 at the bottom. Oh, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 And what room did you have a bathroom in, because I know there weren't bathrooms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Well, I'll tell you the truth about the bath, we had a big round washtub. Friday, of course, had to be bath}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12532078\charrsid12671005  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 night and my mother had a hefty job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Where did she heat the water?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 On the gas stove, so far as I know. I think we had a gas stove then In any case they had what they call a {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname 
City}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}kitchener{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, that's a kitchen range with a fire and the oven and all the top, to, heat the water on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Did you have clean clothes on a set day of the week, or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 So far as I know everything was clean on a Sunday. Everybody had to be, you know, fitted up on a Sunday. My mother wasn't \'85
 what shall I say? She didn't force us into any church or any religion but we automatically fell into it, you know what I mean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 I'd like to ask you some things about mealtimes in those days. Where did the family have their meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Well, naturally, in the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Did you ever eat in any other room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 No, not to my knowledge.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 You never ate in the front room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Unless we had a party of some sort, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 You say that your mother had a {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}kitchener{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose} and did she have gas at the same time as she had that, did you say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Well, I've forgotten now, to tell you the truth, but I expect we did. I don't think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Did you have breakfast in the morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Always had breakfast because I had to go out to work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Could you tell me what you had in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Well it didn't go much past bread and butter in those days.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Anything to drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Well, the usual tea, you know. Tea or cocoa.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 And did you all have the meal together? What members of the family were there for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Well, of course, two \'85 3 of us used to}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6447358\charrsid12671005  \{blank\}}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005  used to go out at 8 o'clock in the morning which meant it left it clear for the younger ones to have theirs soon after 8. Soon as we were out of the way. 'Course, they had to go to school at 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 9}}}9 o'clock{\*\xmlclose}, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 What about your father, did he eat with you older ones that had to go out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Well, me father, I told you. He started work at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}
{\xmlattrvalue 0}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 18}}}6 o'clock{\*\xmlclose} in the morning at Ealing. He always took his breakfast with him. And dinner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 What did he take with him for breakfast and dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Well, sandwiches, I suppose. I can't tell you any more.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 What about the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 12}}}midday{\*\xmlclose} meal? Did the family come home for that, the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Yes, so far as I know we were all home, more or less, to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}
{\xmlattrvalue 0}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 12}}}midday{\*\xmlclose} meal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 I remember you saying that your mother was good at cheap cuts, and that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Well, couldn't get anything else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 She knew hot to cook them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 She had to cook them, of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 And in the evening did you have a meal together, the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Well, I believe we did. Yes, I believe we were all at home together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 What did you have then, in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Not much past the old bread and butter}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6447358\charrsid12671005  \{blank\}}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 , or bread and jam
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Yes, I know, that's what we want to find out. And you did have meat at midday, you said?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Oh, yes, we had \'85 mostly a stew, you know. Well, as you said, mostly the cheaper cuts.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Did your mother ever make anything to have afterwards, a pudding or anything of that kind?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Not, I don't remember a great lot about what you'd call afters. Sunday, of course, we had a cake.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 And did you have a different kind of meat on Sunday, or was it stew?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Oh, we generally had a roast on a Sunday, or some such, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Did you have anything extra for breakfast on a Sunday, or was it bread and butter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Well, I tell you, we'd got no choice, you know. That's how they were brought up in those days. No, I don't remember anything else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Do you remember your mother making jam, or making anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Oh, yes, she used to make a little bit of jam, but not a great lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Did you have fruit trees in the garden? Or in the allotment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Just vegetables, were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Do you know if she made any pickles or anything of that kind?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Well, she what I call dabbled about with them when she could. Nothing in particular.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Did your mother and father eat different food from the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Never to my knowledge.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 They all had the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Did they ever say Grace at meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 No, I don't think they ever did, but then, I suppose they may have done Well, when I say it made no difference, there was that difference.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Could I ask you a few questions about behaviour at table, because customs have changed. Were you allowed to talk during meals.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Well, there were no restrictions in our house. If my mother saw somebody misbehaving themselves, they had it! It didn't do us any harm

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 You could choose, then, what you wanted to eat, could you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 At meal, if she served up something you didn't fancy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Well, we were a good healthy crowd and we were glad to eat anything. I don't think we minded too much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 And could you ask for more if there was more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12532078\charrsid12671005  If it }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 was there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 And you were allowed to ask for it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Well, my mother used to ask us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Was she particular about how you handled your knife and fork and spoon, and that kind of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Well, we had natural training, and expect somebody, you know \'85
 somebody went wrong at some time or other and she just told them where to get off.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Were you allowed to bring a toy or a book, if you had one, to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Not to my knowledge, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 When could you leave the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Well, we usually more or less all left together. I don't think we had any stipulated time, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Did you all have the same places?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Generally, we got in the same place each day, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Could you tell me how your mother served the meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Well, she used to serve it, far as I know from the cent}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12532078\charrsid12671005 re}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005  of the table. You know what I mean to say. There were the 6 or 7 plates and she would go all the way round. I can't tell you anything else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 
When there were young children in the family, you know, at the stage where they still needed to be fed, were they fed separately from the rest of you, before you had your meal, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 
No, I think we were all there together. One would sit on Mum's knee and she would feed 'em with a spoon, or whatever. Oh, no, as far as I know we all had it together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Was your mother an easy person to get along with, to talk to? Did you find her an easy person to talk to? Were you close to her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 She was very good. She was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 How did your parents expect you and your brothers and sisters to behave towards them?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Well, I'll tell you quite candidly about it. There was no real exp
ectations of good behaviour. There was a crowd of us. Well, I tell you there were 7 of us. We were all more or less \'85 you know \'85
. I don't say perfect, but that's just how we used to treat our mother. We'd never cross her if we could help it. Oh, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 
Suppose, say, you got into a bit of a fight with another child, or one of your brothers and sisters did, and the other child hit you, what would your mother or father say if you told them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Do you mean of the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 No, I mean another child at school. You know the sort of things that are happening all the time with children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 
We had our scraps and say nothing, unless we came home with a black eye, or something. 'Hallo, what have you been doing?', you know, when we used to come home. 'Well, I suppose you asked for it'. That was it! We didn't expect sympathy, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 But would they tell you, generally, in life, to hit back if you were hit, or to turn the other cheek, sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 No, I don't remember them ever telling us that. We used to hit back, and that was it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 
You said they had no expectations of good behaviour, but what sort of things did they bring you up - even if it wasn't talked about - they must have brought you up to think certain things were important in life, worth
 caring about. Could you tell me something about what you think they thought was important in life. The important things about how you should live.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Do you mean from a spiritual point of view?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Yes, that sort of thing. And general manners and behaviour, and how to eat and everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 
Well, I can't tell you too much about that. But my mother probably took it for granted that we learnt what there was to be learnt at school and it was naturally ingrained in us. Strictly speaking we'd been no trouble to her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 When you did do something your parents disapproved of, did they punish you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Yes, my father had a strap, and I felt it (laughter)
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Did he use it often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Not a great lot, no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 And your mother, would she punish you, too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Oh, she'd give us one of them; 'Oh, I hurt meself more when I hurt you'. That's what she used to say. That's what she used to say!
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Can you remember, as a family together, if there were ever things you did altogether? Did you all go out together,
 or do anything all together, all of you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Well, I don't know as Mum and Dad used to take us out a great lot for picnics, but we used to go out, generally, well \'85
 Churchfields over the way, there. If we'd got 2 or 3 bottles of water, or something like that and a few bits of bread and butter we were satisfied. That was our picnic. One day a year we'd manage a day down at the seaside.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Would that be organised by your mother and father, or by some other \'85?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Well, the St. Johns Temperance Society used to be in Ealing. They had their regular outings and \'85
. Well, that was our holiday, that was. We didn't really have a holiday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 And when you went on that {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}St. John's{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose} Temperance outing, was it just the children, or did your mother and father go as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Oh, my parents went with them, oh, yes, to look after them for the day. Yes, we could go down to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
Weston-Super-Mare{\*\xmlclose} for 4 shillings return in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 What vehicle was that in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Great Western Railway. They'd charter a train.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Do you ever remember being taken by your mother or father to visit friends or neighbours, or relations? Going out visiting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Oh, yes. We had relations the other side of {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}London
{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, in Camberwell. And they used to come to see us and we used to go to see them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 How often would that be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 That's be once or twice a year, perhaps.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 When they came, how long would they stay for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Well, if they came Christmas time - 'course, you could travel then on a Christmas day, which you can't do now - they'd com
e along, the family of, oh, somewhere about 5 or 6 youngsters, this, that and the other}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6309724\charrsid12671005 .}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 
 Well, they didn't go home Christmas night. They laid all over the shop, you know what I mean to say. We used to call it. Well, we'd lay on the floor, put a spare mattr
ess down, and they'd go home the next day. And they thoroughly enjoyed their Christmas round the old piano.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 You had a piano, did you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Sing songs, and that. Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Who would play the piano?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Well, 2 or 3 of them. I can't tell you exactly. I could play with one finger.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 How many were there? How many were these relations, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Oh, there'd be about 7, I expect.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 What relations were they to you? Was it your mother's side?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 My mother's brother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Did they always come to you at Christmas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Mostly always. Mostly always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 And when you went there, did you also spend the night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Yes, yes, we did the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 I wanted to ask you if you remember your father taking an interest in politics at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 I don't think he ever did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 And your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 In those days, you know, they kept to their house, and that. Outside of their house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 So you don't even know what his views were? What he felt about the government?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 No, I cannot tell you really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Do you remember your father going to watch sport, at all, or going to the races? That sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 No, he wasn't interested in sport to my knowledge. Horse-racing and that,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Did he do anything outside the home at all, other than the allotment? Did he have a club, or go to a club regularly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 No, he didn't. he had his pint of beer on a Sunday, but that was all he had. No, no, he used to come home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 And your mother? You mentioned she used to go to the Mothers' Meeting.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Apart from that I don't think she ever had anything else.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 That was her main activity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Yes.
