therwise no. Just in the run of neighbourliness. It was quite good, too, in those days. Everybody knew each other and this was quite a short street and everyone knew each other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 It wasn't a kind of organised social life? I mean, people would just drop in, would they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 That's right. Nothing really organised. Well, we hadn't got the organised clubs then, in them days, you know, they weren't there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 But you wouldn't say to somebody 'will you come round to my house on such and such a day', that so
rt of thing, would you? Would it be planned in advance?
