anned on regular evenings or regular days people would get together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 No, nothing really regular about it. They were just ordinary type of neighbourliness that used to go down very well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 You were saying, when you were talking about conditions then, that you were what you would call a working class family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 And what other classes at that time, how would you think that the other classes were? In {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}England{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, then, around where you lived?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Well, I can only explain it in one way. We ha
d the working class, we had the middle class and we had the aristocrats. There were 3 types of people in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 And in the area where you lived, did you come into personal contact with members of the middle class and the aristocracy yourself?
