ates. No, I didn't recognise that! I tell you, I got mixed up with, I might say, the middle class people, that's what Hanwell consisted of, the other side of Hanwell and, well, I got along well with them. I treated them with respect because \'85
 well, one reason was this, I used to meet them every day and they were the customers I used to call on and that's just what you'd expect. But they never \'85
 they didn't mix up much with this side of the parish. This side of the parish is distinctly Hanwell, the other part is just that wee bit above
