}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Maunder Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}? Did you ever come into personal contact with him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 
Yes. And what I remember he was Sidney Barnes, I think, the surveyor to the Hanwell Council. I believe he was the landlord. That's the best of my recollection, mind you, I'm not too sure.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Do you remember how your parents and you considered him as a landlord, what your feelings were about him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Well, the landlord was the landlord, and that was it. He'd come along and collect the rent, and apart from that \'85
 well, I don't remember much else. No, we didn't expect much else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 I think you said that your father passed over in 1914?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 1914 it was, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 What effect did that have on the family? I mean from a financial point of view?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Well, we mostly had to live the best we could. Nothing else for it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 How did you manage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 
There could have been about 3 or 4 of us at work, paying our usual quota, which was anything from 10 to 12/6 a week, something like that, that's how it used to be in those days, and \'85. Well, it wasn't too good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Did you ever get any help from anybody else, or any outside agency like the Guardians, that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 No. My mother had a dread of what they called The Parish in those days and so did most people. Do anything but, you know, keep away from }
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6309724\charrsid12671005 T}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 he Parish, even though they were starving to death. Independence \'85
 well, you wouldn't credit it I remember my mother, she took over \'85 well, it wouldn't be allowed, now without being registered \'85 minding babies all day. Women that used to go out to work, they used to pay her s
o much, perhaps a shilling a day and that used to help her along. They'd come and bring them in the morning and they'd collect them at night and that's how she used to carry on \'85 look after them for a few shillings a week
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 How many babies would she have at one time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 
Anywhere from 4 to 6, I should imagine. She had her full day then. But she was glad of the money, and that was it. But now, of course, they have to be registered and all that. She wouldn't be allowed to do it now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 When you were at school, were your parents interested in your school work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 
Well, they were naturally interested up to a point, you know what I mean to say. I can't tell you any more. They used to like to see us go from standard to standard. They used to work in sta
ndards then, you know. We had 7 standards in our school. You went from one to the other, well they were naturally pleased and that's \'85 you know, as far as taking an interest in us\'85 Well, parents' associations as we know them today didn't exist.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Do you
 remember at the school if the teachers single out some children for different treatment from others, or did they treat you all the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Well, I don't remember any real distinction.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Did you have any children from a Union come into the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 No, what they call the scattered homes, they didn't exist in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 
Do you remember any children who were excluded by the other children? I don't mean by the teachers, but who were left out of things, sort of after classes, in the school? Or was it all quite friendly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 No. Of course, that all depended on the teacher. You'd have certain boys, perhaps, 'he's one of Mr.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6309724\charrsid12671005  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14365578\charrsid12671005 \{blank\}}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 
 good boys', and this, that and the other, you know, but we didn't take too much notice. We all got on very well. W
e had some jolly good teachers and they didn't treat us bad. If we wanted 6 of the best, well, we had 'em! (laughter) We didn't take too much notice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 When you were working full time as a greengrocer, how did you get along with the other people you worked with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Well, there was 3 boys; we were all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 And your employer, how did you get along with him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Oh, very well. Very well. And the two daughters, oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Was it a family business, then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 It was a family, yes. Opposite the Town \'85 by the bus depot. I was there for 3 years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 In the War did you go away?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Yes, three years and a half; {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}France{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose} and Belgium.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 What year did you go away, then? In '15?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 May.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 In 1915, May?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Yes. I didn't actually go away, I was kept at home for training. '16, I went away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 I think you said that your wife had been in domestic service before she married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 And then she went back and worked at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}McLeans{\*\xmlclose}?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Well, she went on war work in Cambridge
 Yard, you can almost see her here, making steel springs. That little factory is still there. And it was so unpleasant they used to come all \'85 you know, the perspiration, and that, they were \'85
 oh, everything with iron mould, they couldn't keep any clothes 
on, you know. And then she went down to McLeans and I forget how long she stopped down there, but that got too much for her and she had to come home. Conveyor belts don't suit everybody, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Did she work before your first child was born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Yes, a little domestic work, go out to \'85
 go out in the mornings. Half a crown for a morning, disgraceful pay, but that's what they used to get. A long morning, too, I should think it was. Hard work at that, too. They hadn't got the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Hoover{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} cleaners then, you know. Oh, they had a rough time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 It was a daughter first, wasn't it? The first child you had was a daughter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 It was, yes, she was 52 years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 After she was born did your wife go back to work again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 I forget whether she took over \'85. dom
estic work or not, but I believe she used to take the baby with her. Oh, no, she used to leave the baby with my mother. My mother looked after the baby.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 What age was the baby when she first left her with your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Oh, quite a baby, 'cos I was at the War and she wanted the money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Were you at home when your daughter was born? Or were you at the War then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 I was at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 How did your wife manage, did she have a doctor?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Yes, she had a doctor and a midwife, an old friend of ours. A really good sort, she was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 And can you remember at that time did she have any neighbours, or anyone coming in to help her? In the house, after the baby was born?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Well, we had one really good neighbour, lived a short distance up the road, a
nd we had one upstairs. Another really good neighbour. Downstairs, I should've said. She still lives there now, {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Oaklands Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
, that's the second from here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 And she used to help, did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Well, you know, do \'85. they'd come in. Look in different times of the day, that's what it amounted to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 How many years did you have together before you went off to the War? About 2 to 3 years, did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Oh, I was married in 1913. That would make 3 years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Did you help your wife in the house at all, or did you do gardening like your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Well, I did the jobs that I thought I could do, and that was the main point about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 What sort of jobs did you do in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Well, usually washing up. If she wasn't too well, I'd carry on, that's all I can tell you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Did you do anything for the little girl? Did you look after the little girl in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Oh, if I could push her out in the pram, that was my delight, that was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 You liked doing that, did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 I did, oh, yes. I was never too proud to push a pram.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Did you and your wife talk about how you were going to bring her up and what the right thing to do was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 After the war generations tended to marry younger and they more or less \'85.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Are you talking about the First War now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 
After both Wars, and the man took over duties, at least in my estimation including pushing the pram, what you see today, what they didn't attempt to do before 1914.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 So you were exceptional at that time in pushing a pram, were you do you think?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 I won't tell you that, but in any case, that suited me (laughter).
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Did you still live in Hanwell?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 I've lived in Hanwell 79 years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 So those rooms that you got when you got married, were they near where your mother's home was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Oh, no, no. They were over there. Not too far away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 
Did you keep up the same pattern of life as you'd had at home, dropping in with neighbours, and that sort of thing? Did you have neighbours in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Well, we naturally made the contacts, that was a recognised thing then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Did your wife's mother ever come and visit her? She was living in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Wales{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, I believe?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 She lived at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Bangor{\*\xmlclose}, {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}North Wales{\*\xmlclose}
, which meant that she couldn't come very often. We used to spend our holidays there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 How long was that, that you'd spend there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Well, we only had a week's holiday in those days, you know and that was it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Did you go every year there, to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Bangor{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose}?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Oh, quite a number of years, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Did you and your wife had the same ideas a
bout how to bring up children, and what was right for children, or did you differ on some points?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Well, I don't remember differing at all. We naturally brought them up as we thought they would go, and that was it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 But you agreed on what children should be allowed to do and shouldn't?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 
Well, they turned out as perfect as ever any man can expect, and that's it. I can't tell you any more. We always went out together, the boy and the girl, and \'85. well, of course, there was 10 years difference be
tween the boy and the girl, so that had something to do with it. But the fact remains we were all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 And when your wife had to leave the baby and go out to work, she left it, did you say, with your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Did it worry her that she had to leave the baby, or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Well, there's no doubt that it did. She didn't like doing it, but she knew the baby was in good hands and it's that what counted.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 And you, yourself, did it distress you that she had to leave the baby, or did you feel the same as she did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Well, I'd got no option. I'd got to go out to work all day, and that was it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 And after the war ended, did she continue working?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 No, she didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Did she ever go back to work at any other period in her life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 No. No, she'd got the boy and the girl to look after, and that was it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 And you yourself became a railway}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid404293\charrsid12671005  man}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Quite true, that was in 1920.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Did you stay on in that work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Until 1956, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 What occupation did your son have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 
Well, he was a rather scientific sort of a chap. He made up his mind to get mixed up with the electronic business. He went out at the age of 14 a place called Pullens, had a place in West Ealing, there, they've got the big firm, now, in the Gt. West Road
, Brentford, and got a job there. Well, he stayed in that class of business. He got married and went to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}St. Albans{\*\xmlclose} to live. That's where he is today. He's working now for Marconi's which is quite a \'85
 they're in quite a big way, a branch of the General Electric. Yes, he's on the staff and so far as I know he's got a job for life now. Well, he's engaged quite a lot now in these giant computers, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10243417 \'a3}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 25,000 each, you know. It's astonishing what there is in one of these computers. In any case, that's his life and t
hat's it. He'll sit down and make you a television set over the weekend and not turn a hair. He made his first wireless set when he was 10 years of age. I didn't persuade him in any way. I said, 'You've got your life to lead, get on with it'. Well, he's g
ot to make his way without my help.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 What about your daughter, what work did she do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 
Now the daughter, she went to W. H. Smith's bookstall for some years and then she went as a receptionist to an optician in Bond St., Ealing. Then she got married, and that was it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 She didn't work after she was married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 
I wonder if you could also tell me what jobs your brothers had. I've got this bit of paper here. For example, there's Alf, what work did he do?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Well, he started as a gardener and finished as a postman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Did he do anything in between?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 No, no, he just had those two.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 And George?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 George was a bricklayer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 All his life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Well, he died at the age of 22, that's the unfortunate part about that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 And Fred?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Fred, well what I remember of him, he was in the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}West Ealing{\*\xmlclose}
 railway depot as a junior clerk. That's what I remember of him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 And your sisters; is the first one written here Nell?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 What work did she do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Well, you see, there wasn't a great number of \'85
 choice much, in those days. It was either laundry or domestic service. Well, she went to work in Troy Laundry, {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}West Ealing{\*\xmlclose}. That doesn't exist now, they pulled it down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Did she always do that kind of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Yes, until she was married.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 And Jennie?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 
Well, there's a big orphan school the other side of the parish, or used to be, belonging to the Borough of Southwark, the other side of London. Well, that's not in existence now, an L.C.C. estate's
 being built on it now, going to be a thousand houses over there, on the other side of the parish. Well, she was a laundry maid in that orphanage.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Did she ever do any other kind of work, or was that all she did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Far as I know that was all she did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 And Mabel, what did she do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 
Well Mabel, she stated down at Fairey Aviation works, down at Hayes, then she went nursing. Oh, she must have spent 30 years nursing, finished up as an maternity sister in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
West{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Middlesex{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}Hospital{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, after a term at Hammersmith, Hammersmith Hospital.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 
I meant to ask you about the kind of food that your wife and you had in those first few years you were married, you know, in the period up to before you went to the War. Did you have the same kind of food that you'd had at home, the same sort of meals?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 
Well, no, we naturally lived better because there wasn't so many of us. Oh, no, we had quite a good variety. We had the usual, you know. We had a sweet afterwards. Oh, yes. Oh, no, there's no distinction, not with
 anyone in the family compared with some of them today. No distinction. We can't compare the two.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 For breakfast, for example, did you have more than bread and butter then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Oh, we went on to cereals. Oh, yes. Well, we had all the meals then, as I suppose, probably we have today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 For tea, for example, what would you have, when you were first married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Well, there was always a knick-knack of some sort, you know. Salads, and \'85 oh, yes, yes, there would be.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Did you have any garden, or allotment, when you were married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Not when I was married in 1913.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 So you didn't have any means of growing anything to eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 And did your wife have a routine at all? I remember you said your mother had Monday washday, did your wife h
ave a sort of housework routine that she followed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 More or less the old routine in those days, you know, even at my daughter's you know, Monday has to be washing day for most people now. }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid404293\charrsid12671005 I}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 t never alters, ever.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 When you were married did you continue going to the same Church, {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}St.{\*\xmlclose}
 Mary's, I think you said?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Yes, I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Did your wife attend the same one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 She was Church of England so she'd come, well, quite a number of times. I started my little daughter there, she was about 3 years ol
d when I took her over to the old parish church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 You took her along to services, did you, your little daughter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 I used to take her out, of course.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 She was very young to be taken.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Never mind. She went and I used to take her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 She could keep quiet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Quiet enough. She was no trouble.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 You mentioned how you used to have sing-songs round the piano. Did your wife play the piano or any musical instrument?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 She never had lessons, but she could always knock a tune out. That's the only way to put it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16258992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Did you have a piano in your first home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2108855 JT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3553086\charrsid12671005 Yes, I had a piano. When my daughter got married I gave it to her.
